# Cursor Rules for my portfolio site
# Mode: Minimalist • Modern • Portfolio-focused

## Goal
Keep token usage minimal. Do NOT load large or irrelevant files. Only modify the key front-end files. Bias toward clean, accessible, fast UI.

## Read scope (allow)
- index.html
- style.css
- bootstrap.js
- images/**/*.{png,jpg,jpeg,svg,gif,webp,avif}   # READ-ONLY (for dimensions/alt text checks)

## Write scope (strict)
- index.html
- style.css
- bootstrap.js
# Do not create, delete, or edit any other files.

## Conditional single-file allow
+ public/favicon.ico    # READ-ONLY

## Hard excludes (NEVER READ)
- node_modules/**
- .git/**
- dist/**
- build/**
- .next/**
- .cache/**
- coverage/**
- assets/**
- public/**                           # (except favicon above)
- **/*.{mp4,mov,mkv,avi,zip,tar,gz,7z,mp3,wav,flac,pdf,psd,ai}
- **/*.map
- **/*.lock
- **/*.{ttf,otf,woff,woff2}
- **/*.{blend,fbx,glb,gltf,stl}
- **/*.{csv,jsonl,parquet}
- **/.DS_Store
- **/Thumbs.db

## Token discipline
- Prefer local reasoning. Skip files > 500KB.
- Do NOT recursively scan directories unless path matches an allow-list.
- “Review the project” = summarize ONLY from index.html, style.css, bootstrap.js (plus small images if relevant).
- If a change requires disallowed files or new assets, STOP and ask permission.
- Do NOT fetch remote content or upgrade libs without explicit permission.
- Avoid vendor/minified code; if unavoidable, read a tiny, relevant slice.

## Editing style
- Keep diffs minimal/localized. No broad reformatting.
- Preserve existing semantics and structure; avoid stylistic churn.
- For non-trivial changes, include a short, clear diff message (what/why).
- Use HTML comments to mark edit blocks so future diffs stay focused:
  <!-- @cursor-start: <short-purpose> --> ... <!-- @cursor-end -->

## Design assistant behavior (NEW)
- Favor minimalist visual language: ample whitespace, strong hierarchy, subtle motion.
- Propose at most TWO variant options per change, embedded as commented snippets (no new files).
- Prefer utility-like, composable CSS over one-off styles; avoid duplication.
- If design requires assets (icons/illustrations), suggest system emoji/unicode or CSS shapes first; otherwise ASK before adding files.

## Accessibility (A11y) guardrails (NEW)
- Enforce semantic HTML: <header>, <main>, <section>, <footer>, <nav>, <figure>, <figcaption>.
- All interactive elements must be <button>, <a>, or form controls; no <div role="button"> unless justified in a diff message.
- Ensure color-contrast ≥ 4.5:1 for text; if not, adjust CSS variables and explain in diff message.
- Add skip links: a visually-hidden “Skip to content” anchor at top.
- Respect reduced motion: wrap non-essential animations in
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) { /* animations */ }
- Images: require alt text. Decorative images must have alt="".

## Performance budgets (NEW)
- Avoid layout thrashers in JS (repeated sync reads/writes); batch with requestAnimationFrame.
- No blocking webfonts; use system stack in CSS (see Typography below).
- Images: prefer width/height attributes and CSS object-fit; avoid 4K assets; suggest WebP if existing size > 300KB (do not transform yourself).
- Cap total added CSS to ≤ 200 lines per PR unless explicitly approved.
- No inline <style> or style="" attributes; consolidate in style.css.

## Information architecture (NEW)
- Keep top-level sections limited and scannable: {Hero, About, Experience/Projects, Selected Work, Contact}.
- Each section should start with a single <h2> and a short intro (≤ 2 lines).
- Prefer cards or simple lists; avoid carousels and heavy components.

## CSS architecture & tokens (NEW)
- Define and reuse CSS variables in :root; allow edits in style.css only.
  :root {
    /* Brand */
    --bg: #0b0c0f;           /* or current */
    --fg: #e6e7eb;
    --muted: #9aa0aa;
    --accent: #5b8cff;       /* single accent */
    /* Layout */
    --maxw: 72rem;
    --radius: 14px;
    --gap: 1.25rem;
    /* Typography scale */
    --fs-900: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    --fs-700: clamp(1.5rem, 2.5vw, 2rem);
    --fs-400: 1rem;
    --lh: 1.6;
  }
- Use a system font stack for speed:
  font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, Ubuntu, Cantarell, "Helvetica Neue", Arial, "Noto Sans", "Apple Color Emoji", "Segoe UI Emoji", "Segoe UI Symbol", sans-serif;
- Limit selector depth to 3; avoid !important.
- Naming: prefer BEM-ish or low-specificity utilities (e.g., .container, .grid, .btn, .tag).
- Provide responsive rules at these breakpoints only:
  @media (max-width: 960px) { ... }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { ... }

## Layout patterns (NEW)
- Container rule: .container { max-width: var(--maxw); margin-inline: auto; padding-inline: 1rem; }
- Grid helper: .grid { display: grid; gap: var(--gap); grid-template-columns: repeat(12, 1fr); }
  Use span classes (e.g., .col-6) in CSS, not inline styles.
- Spacing scale: use multiples of 4px; round to 2 decimals in rems.

## Motion & micro-interactions (NEW)
- Keep transitions ≤ 180ms for most UI; 240ms for larger elements.
- Use transform/opacity; avoid animating layout properties (top/left/width/height).
- Hover/focus states must be distinct in both color and outline.

## JavaScript behavior (NEW)
- Keep JS idempotent; re-runnable without duplicating listeners or DOM.
- Defer non-critical JS; attach listeners after DOMContentLoaded.
- Route all UI tweaks through bootstrap.js; do not introduce new files.
- Avoid global namespace pollution; use IIFE or a single app namespace.

## SEO & metadata (NEW)
- Ensure <title>, meta[name="description"], canonical link, and Open Graph/Twitter tags exist in index.html.
- Add JSON-LD Organization/Person if helpful, but keep within index.html only; no external fetches.

## Content heuristics (NEW)
- Hero: one-liner value prop (≤ 12 words) + 1 CTA button + 1 secondary link.
- Project cards: title, 1-sentence impact, 3 compact bullets (problem → approach → outcome).
- Avoid walls of text; prefer lists and short paragraphs.

## Review checklists Cursor should run mentally before proposing changes (NEW)
- A11y: headings order valid? landmarks present? focus ring visible?
- Perf: any added oversized images/CSS? fonts system-only? scripts deferred?
- Readability: line length 60–80ch on desktop? adequate spacing?
- Consistency: colors/spacing/typography tokens reused? no duplicates?

## Bootstrap & scripts guidance
- Assume frontend behavior is defined in bootstrap.js; edit there first.
- Do NOT add build steps, bundlers, or dependencies.
- Do NOT inject external CDNs/scripts unless explicitly approved.

## Images policy
- READ-ONLY for reference (dimensions/alt). Do NOT inline/compress/transform.
- If optimization is beneficial, suggest exact filenames + target sizes in a comment; do not modify files.

## Commit/diff messages (NEW)
- Prefix: [Design], [A11y], [Perf], or [Content].
- Keep subject ≤ 72 chars, body ≤ 5 lines, include rationale + before/after summary.

## Safety rails
- If rules conflict, the stricter rule wins (deny > allow).
- When in
